-- FACTBOX: PepsiCo offers to buy bottlers in $6 billion deal
-- 
-- Mon Apr 20, 2009 6:21am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/04/20/us-pepsico-factbox-sb-idUSTRE53J1Q920090420

 

 (Reuters) - PepsiCo Inc ( PEP.N ), the world's No. 2 maker of soft drinks, has proposed buying the outstanding shares it does not own in its two largest bottlers, Pepsi Bottling Group PBG.N and PepsiAmericas PAS.N, in a $6 billion cash and stock deal. 

 Following is a summary of details of the deal: TERMS * $29.50 per share in cash and stock for Pepsi Bottling * $23.27 per share in cash and stock PepsiAmericas * Offer represents 17 pct premium to Friday's close EXISTING RELATIONSHIP * PepsiCo owns 33.1 percent of the outstanding common stock and 100 percent of the outstanding Class B common stock in Pepsi Bottling, as of February 13 * PepsiCo owns about 54 million shares in PepsiAmericas, or 43.2 percent of common stock, as of March 10 FINANCIAL HEALTH? PepsiCo cash and cash equivalents as of March 21 -- $2.19 billion PepsiCo long-term debt obligations as of March 21 -- $9.24 billion PepsiCo shares outstanding as of March 21 -- 1.57 billion Pepsi Bottling FY 2008 net income of $162 million, or $0.74/share PepsiAmericas FY 2008 net income of $226.4 million, or $1.78/share (Reporting by Jennifer Robin Raj in Bangalore; Editing by Rupert Winchester)